text.section:
All offenses under this chapter classified as violations shall be prepayable except for:
Any offense that could result in license suspension or revocation by the court or the Transportation Cabinet;
Any offense relating to KRS 189.393, 189.520, or 189.580;
When the defendant is speeding in a restricted zone;
When the defendant is speeding more than twenty-five (25) miles per hour over the posted speed limit under KRS 189.394;
An offense where evidence of the offense or of commission of another offense is seized by the officer and the citation is so marked and a court date set;
The offense is cited with another offense that is not prepayable;
When the defendant is under the age of eighteen (18); or
An arrest is made under KRS 431.015.
